{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1f7502b4-8504-4476-8e40-575b147708fb","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax\nMTP uses `--filter` but with **different operators**. The VSTest `~` (contains) and `&` (and) become:\n\n| VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~X` | `FullyQualifiedName contains X` |\n| `&` | `&` (same) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `Category=Smoke` (same) |\n\nYour new CI command:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName contains IntegrationTests & Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### 2. Trait attribute\nxUnit v3 dropped `[Trait(\"Category\", \"...\")]` in favor of a built-in `[Category]` attribute. Update your test class:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_015EzoCkXs9PkNKs1RvWAwWW","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-bd37785524c641c0b9990367f298ace2/IntegrationTests.cs","old_str":"[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]","new_str":"[Category(\"Smoke\")]"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-bd37785524c641c0b9990367f298ace2/IntegrationTests.cs."}],"interactionId":"6164bb66-4c3e-419a-8d9c-ab954dc4358e","outputTokens":343,"requestId":"0428:1CDF9E:1ED11D3:22B0B6A:69E81BDF"},"id":"9616eef9-473e-4f38-8a8a-0f224cef8812","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:52:53.938Z","parentId":"f2b48f25-02da-45bb-9faa-9a5cd878f8d4"}
